1
00:00:00,640 --> 00:00:01,810
It's an unknown number.

2
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:04,380
(Episode 132)

3
00:00:04,840 --> 00:00:06,580
Yes, this is Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

4
00:00:06,580 --> 00:00:07,580
Yes.

5
00:00:08,350 --> 00:00:09,380
Yes, this is he.

6
00:00:11,050 --> 00:00:12,050
I'm sorry?

7
00:00:13,050 --> 00:00:15,750
Are you Ma Dong Seok, the Chairman's son?

8
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:17,960
Ma Dong Seok?

9
00:00:18,860 --> 00:00:21,630
- That's my biological father's name.
- Yes.

10
00:00:22,130 --> 00:00:23,160
Yes, I understand.

11
00:00:26,030 --> 00:00:27,100
What's going on?

12
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:30,700
Was that really my father
you were just talking to?

13
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,170
Yes, Jang Mi.

14
00:00:32,440 --> 00:00:35,110
The person on the phone just now
was your father.

15
00:00:35,940 --> 00:00:38,080
But I thought my father was dead.

16
00:00:38,510 --> 00:00:41,950
I was told he went missing
before Seo Rin and I were even born.

17
00:00:43,180 --> 00:00:45,880
Is my father really alive?

18
00:00:45,980 --> 00:00:48,890
Yes, he is. He just arrived in Korea.

19
00:00:49,020 --> 00:00:50,790
You should be able to see him soon.

20
00:00:52,460 --> 00:00:56,930
Apparently, the Chairman has been in
contact with your father for a long time.

21
00:00:57,130 --> 00:00:59,900
The Chairman told him to contact me,
his lawyer, if anything happened.

22
00:01:00,170 --> 00:01:01,570
That's how he got my number.

23
00:01:02,130 --> 00:01:05,440
He rushed to Korea when he heard
that the Chairman had collapsed.

24
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:20,750
Excuse me.

25
00:01:21,590 --> 00:01:24,220
Are you waiting for me?

26
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:40,840
Dong Seok?

27
00:01:42,370 --> 00:01:43,680
Is it really...

28
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:46,280
you, Dong Seok?

29
00:01:57,020 --> 00:01:58,520
It's been a long time, Suk Hee.

30
00:02:00,290 --> 00:02:01,460
Dong Seok.

31
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:04,100
Is it you, Dong Seok?

32
00:02:06,530 --> 00:02:07,530
How...

33
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,800
How...

34
00:02:11,970 --> 00:02:12,970
Yes, that's right.

35
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,040
It's your husband,

36
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:19,440
Ma Dong Seok.

37
00:02:23,450 --> 00:02:24,450
Suk Hee.

38
00:02:28,090 --> 00:02:29,150
Dong Seok.

39
00:02:31,490 --> 00:02:32,860
I'm very late, aren't I?

40
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:34,760
I'm sorry, Suk Hee.

41
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:37,100
I'm so sorry.

42
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:42,530
Is it really...

43
00:02:44,670 --> 00:02:46,270
Is it really you, Dong Seok?

44
00:02:47,810 --> 00:02:51,540
Dong Seok, you're really alive?

45
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:54,210
Yes, Suk Hee.

46
00:02:55,510 --> 00:02:56,650
We used to...

47
00:02:57,380 --> 00:03:00,620
walk along this path holding hands
all the time, remember?

48
00:03:02,690 --> 00:03:03,920
You haven't forgotten me, have you?

49
00:03:05,490 --> 00:03:06,590
Dong Seok.

50
00:03:10,230 --> 00:03:11,530
This isn't a dream, is it?

51
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:13,500
It's not a dream.

52
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:17,400
It's me, Ma Dong Seok,
the one who loves you.

53
00:03:18,770 --> 00:03:20,200
To come back to you,

54
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,770
it took 30 years.

55
00:03:23,810 --> 00:03:26,810
I missed you so much
it felt like my heart was tearing apart.

56
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:28,450
I thought I would die, Suk Hee.

57
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:31,420
Dong Seok, thank you...

58
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:35,250
for being alive.

59
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:37,160
Thank you.

60
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:43,060
Thank you for coming back to me.

61
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,430
Thank you.

62
00:03:47,530 --> 00:03:49,200
Thank you so much.

63
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:50,940
Suk Hee.

64
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:03,550
Father.

65
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:07,320
Father, your son, Dong Seok, is here.

66
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:10,290
I guess I came back too late.

67
00:04:12,690 --> 00:04:13,890
I'm sorry, Father.

68
00:04:15,590 --> 00:04:17,430
Even though we share no blood,

69
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:20,160
you raised me like your own son.

70
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,430
But...

71
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,040
I never got to repay your kindness.

72
00:04:27,610 --> 00:04:29,770
I'm sorry, Father.

73
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:31,940
Dong Seok,

74
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:34,450
don't be so heartbroken.

75
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:36,680
To your father,

76
00:04:37,450 --> 00:04:39,780
who thought his own daughter was dead,

77
00:04:40,490 --> 00:04:43,760
you must have been a great comfort.

78
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:49,430
And now,
his condition is slowly improving.

79
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:51,930
I'm relieved to hear he's getting better.

80
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,200
It's such a relief.

81
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:56,100
Dong Seok.

82
00:04:56,870 --> 00:04:58,940
This is our daughter, Jang Mi.

83
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,520
So you're...

84
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,890
You're Jang Mi.

85
00:05:16,350 --> 00:05:17,360
Yes.

86
00:05:17,990 --> 00:05:18,990
Hello.

87
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:20,730
Yes.

88
00:05:20,730 --> 00:05:21,790
I was...

89
00:05:22,730 --> 00:05:23,930
way too late, right?

90
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,200
No, not at all.

91
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:30,440
I'm just so overwhelmed and grateful
that you're alive.

92
00:05:30,940 --> 00:05:34,340
To only be seeing you
now that you're a grown woman.

93
00:05:36,510 --> 00:05:37,740
I'm sorry, Jang Mi.

94
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,080
Thank you...

95
00:05:44,450 --> 00:05:45,480
for growing up so well.

96
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:47,890
I'm so sorry.

97
00:05:49,050 --> 00:05:51,020
I couldn't even protect you all,

98
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:54,630
and we're only meeting
now that you're all grown up.

99
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,360
I'm sorry, Jang Mi.

100
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,270
No, it's okay.

101
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,600
Just being able to meet you like this...

102
00:06:07,170 --> 00:06:08,670
feels like a dream.

103
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,640
Dong Seok.

104
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,480
Right.

105
00:06:15,380 --> 00:06:17,050
We can catch up on everything later.

106
00:06:17,650 --> 00:06:18,720
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

107
00:06:20,420 --> 00:06:22,790
My father has told me a lot about you.

108
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:27,020
It's a true pleasure
to be able to meet you like this.

109
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:29,290
He's my husband.

110
00:06:30,430 --> 00:06:32,460
I see. You're my son-in-law. Thank you.

111
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:33,630
Thank you for staying by Jang Mi's side...

112
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,600
while I was gone.

113
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:38,140
Of course.

114
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,400
I'm so grateful...

115
00:06:41,110 --> 00:06:42,770
that you've returned
to us alive, Father-in-law.

116
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:48,480
(Dream Hotel, June Cash Flow Statement)

117
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:51,780
Manager Lee.
What are these outstanding payments?

118
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:54,150
Why are they all concentrated
in this month?

119
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:57,520
Weren't the Dream Resort's short-term
loan payments due next month?

120
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:58,790
Well...

121
00:06:59,490 --> 00:07:00,830
After Chairman Ma collapsed,

122
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:03,760
our primary bank notified us
that they won't approve an extension.

123
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:06,400
They said it was for risk management,
but in reality,

124
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:09,530
it seems like they're planning
to cut off our line of credit.

125
00:07:09,770 --> 00:07:11,000
Those bastards.

126
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:13,200
We're out of cash right now.

127
00:07:13,940 --> 00:07:16,570
We're short a total
of four million dollars...

128
00:07:16,570 --> 00:07:17,940
for this month's payroll
and vendor payments.

129
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,580
All this commotion
over mere four million dollars?

130
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:22,610
Selling a few of the collector's stones
in my safe...

131
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:24,250
would have easily gotten me ten million.

132
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:27,520
But because of Oh Jang Mi
and Kang Baek Ho,

133
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:29,020
it all vanished into thin air.

134
00:07:29,350 --> 00:07:30,720
I can't believe them.

135
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:33,390
I'm so furious I can't think straight.

136
00:07:35,030 --> 00:07:36,390
Get me four million dollars
in cash right now,

137
00:07:36,390 --> 00:07:37,460
I don't care from where.

138
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,430
From loan sharks or third-tier lenders,
I don't care.

139
00:07:39,430 --> 00:07:40,900
Loan sharks are too risky.

140
00:07:40,970 --> 00:07:42,600
Then what do you want me to do?

141
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,640
What if our cash flow stops
when we have no way out?

142
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:48,710
I haven't even been able to start selling
off the prime assets.

143
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:49,710
What do we do now?

144
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:53,240
I'm looking for overseas investors now,
but it will take time.

145
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:55,380
We have to keep the hotel
running smoothly until then...

146
00:07:55,450 --> 00:07:57,550
if we want to sell it for what it's worth.

147
00:07:57,850 --> 00:07:59,720
Do we have to declare bankruptcy
because of four million dollars?

148
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:04,060
Oh my gosh.

149
00:08:04,690 --> 00:08:05,920
Come on, Mom.

150
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,760
You've just had a difficult reunion
with your husband.

151
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:10,730
You're just serving him stew?
You should have made something special.

152
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:15,800
This is what I used to make
for Dong Seok all the time.

153
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:20,840
This smells incredible.
It's the kimchi stew I've missed so much.

154
00:08:21,410 --> 00:08:24,480
You know, Suk Hee was the first person
to ever make me kimchi stew.

155
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,580
Really?

156
00:08:26,810 --> 00:08:28,780
You really were born with a silver spoon.

157
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:32,980
Come on, let's eat.

158
00:08:36,290 --> 00:08:39,360
By any chance,
I'm not making anyone uncomfortable, am I?

159
00:08:40,490 --> 00:08:41,660
Not at all.

160
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:44,860
We're the ones who are grateful
that you're here.

161
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:48,030
- We're truly happy you're here.
- Thank you.

162
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,340
If you're Jang Mi's father,
that makes you our father too, right?

163
00:08:51,470 --> 00:08:53,740
Oh Bok Gil was a great benefactor to me.

164
00:08:54,310 --> 00:08:58,040
So I'll think of Tae Pyung and Tae Sook...

165
00:08:58,310 --> 00:09:00,210
as my own son and daughter,

166
00:09:00,980 --> 00:09:01,980
so please feel comfortable around me.

167
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:06,220
Grandfather, what about Bo Ra?
Will you love me too?

168
00:09:07,690 --> 00:09:08,690
You just called me Grandfather?

169
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:13,690
Of course. I hope we get along, Bo Ra.

170
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:15,490
Since the family is all together,

171
00:09:15,490 --> 00:09:17,360
let's make a toast,
even if it's with water.

172
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:20,900
Hey, Kang Baek Ho.
You're not part of this family yet.

173
00:09:21,030 --> 00:09:23,330
You're not officially family
until the marriage is registered, are you?

174
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,770
- Come on.
- Hey!

175
00:09:24,770 --> 00:09:28,110
You know Baek Ho and I got married
even though it was just the two of us.

176
00:09:28,340 --> 00:09:30,640
Right, honey?

177
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:33,110
Of course, my dear wife.

178
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:39,450
This really makes me feel like
I'm back in Korea.

179
00:09:39,550 --> 00:09:42,650
It really feels like I've come home.

180
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:43,890
Everyone...

181
00:09:45,460 --> 00:09:49,530
- Thank you.
- We're so glad you've come back safe.

182
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:53,860
- All right. To our family's happiness...
- Cheers.

183
00:09:53,930 --> 00:09:58,140
- Oh my.
- Cheers.

184
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,870
Where did you learn that?

185
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:11,120
- How did it go?
- The situation is serious.

186
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,620
The hotel's accounts...

187
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,690
are completely wiped out.

188
00:10:15,050 --> 00:10:16,720
The employees are threatening
to go on strike...

189
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:19,220
starting tomorrow morning
over unpaid wages.

190
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:20,490
I know!

191
00:10:21,130 --> 00:10:23,290
If the employees strike
before the shareholders' meeting,

192
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:24,860
the board will have my head.

193
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:27,630
I could even be forced out of my position
as interim Chairman.

194
00:10:28,670 --> 00:10:31,340
The funds are gone. What do we do now?

195
00:10:32,140 --> 00:10:34,940
And you don't have the personal funds
to cover this, not even a slush fund.

196
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:38,080
There has to be a way. I'm Chae Hwa Young.

197
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:41,050
Do you have any idea how I clawed my way
into this position?

198
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:44,550
There's no way I'm stepping down.

199
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:48,090
So what happened all this time?

200
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:52,760
For so many years, I thought
you were dead, Dong Seok.

201
00:10:56,290 --> 00:10:58,300
It was when I was on
a business trip to Monaco.

202
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,530
I was on a yacht at night...

203
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,940
when someone hit me hard from behind
and pushed me overboard.

204
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:09,070
- Oh my.
- I fell into the sea and passed out.

205
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:11,980
When I woke up to the bright sunlight,
I was on an unfamiliar yacht.

206
00:11:12,310 --> 00:11:16,280
- So someone saved you, Dad?
- Yes.

207
00:11:16,950 --> 00:11:19,950
Luckily, he was a foreign investor.

208
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:22,850
He was suffering from severe depression...

209
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,790
and was about to end his life
in the middle of the ocean.

210
00:11:25,620 --> 00:11:28,960
And he found me flailing in the water
and pulled me up.

211
00:11:29,430 --> 00:11:30,690
After he saved me,

212
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:32,860
he laughed and said
he couldn't kill himself just to save me.

213
00:11:33,630 --> 00:11:35,570
The problem was,
probably because of my head injury,

214
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:38,200
I couldn't even remember my own name.

215
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:43,510
So all those years, without any memory,
you were struggling in a foreign country?

216
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:47,340
By the time I remembered my name
was Ma Dong Seok and came back to Korea,

217
00:11:48,380 --> 00:11:51,220
you were with that man, Oh Bok Gil,

218
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:54,020
and had a new family.

219
00:11:54,950 --> 00:11:57,320
And next to my father was that woman,
Chae Hwa Young,

220
00:11:58,060 --> 00:11:59,490
acting like the lady of the house.

221
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:02,560
So you just left?

222
00:12:02,990 --> 00:12:04,560
I felt there was no place for me.

223
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:07,030
I was the Chairman's adopted son.

224
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:10,270
I had no desire to live
under the same roof as Chae Hwa Young.

225
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:15,310
Later, the businessman
who saved me passed away.

226
00:12:15,310 --> 00:12:18,510
He left me all his wealth
and a huge investment firm,

227
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:19,980
so I just focused on work.

228
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,710
As time went by,

229
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:24,880
I became curious about
who had hit me from behind...

230
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,920
and pushed me into the sea,

231
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:28,490
so that's when I started to investigate.

232
00:12:28,990 --> 00:12:31,820
But surprisingly, it was Chae Hwa Young.

233
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:35,430
What? Chae Hwa Young?

234
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:37,390
That witch went that far?

235
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:40,970
Chae Hwa Young was after Dream,
so she couldn't have me coming back.

236
00:12:41,070 --> 00:12:44,030
That's why she deliberately sent someone
all the way there to try and kill me.

237
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:47,270
How could she be so cruel?

238
00:12:48,170 --> 00:12:51,410
So you're saying Chae Hwa Young
went after you, too?

239
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:54,410
I called my father right away and warned
him to be careful of Chae Hwa Young.

240
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:57,550
So that's when you started
talking to Grandfather again.

241
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:02,050
That's right.
My father underestimated Chae Hwa Young.

242
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:07,120
He said he was going to take all
of her shares and kick her out penniless.

243
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:09,630
But she got to him
before he had the chance.

244
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:11,360
From now on, no matter what happens,

245
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:15,170
I will protect my family.

246
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:20,670
She took down my father
and killed Seo Rin.

247
00:13:21,470 --> 00:13:23,740
She made my family shed tears of blood.

248
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:28,250
I will drag her to the depths of despair.

249
00:13:29,650 --> 00:13:33,250
Branch Manager.
What do you mean the extension was denied?

250
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:36,090
After all the years Dream has done
business with you,

251
00:13:36,150 --> 00:13:39,490
how can you suddenly demand
repayment in full?

252
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:42,460
I'm sorry, ma'am. The head office's
credit review department...

253
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:44,230
has issued a clear directive.

254
00:13:44,730 --> 00:13:46,960
An extension is absolutely not possible.

255
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:49,470
Just a little longer.
Okay, just one month.

256
00:13:49,530 --> 00:13:52,470
No, just give me two weeks.
Once this shareholders' meeting is over...

257
00:13:52,540 --> 00:13:54,640
Hello? Sir? Hello?

258
00:13:55,210 --> 00:13:56,540
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

259
00:13:56,610 --> 00:13:58,110
Forget our primary bank.

260
00:13:58,310 --> 00:14:00,810
Contact every single tier-one
and tier-two financial institution.

261
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:02,250
Hit up every single one of them.

262
00:14:02,580 --> 00:14:04,320
You have to bring in cash, no matter what.

263
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:11,620
Office Manager? It's me.

264
00:14:13,820 --> 00:14:14,830
Really?

265
00:14:14,830 --> 00:14:17,860
Lee Kang Hyuk is at a bar
by himself right now?

266
00:14:19,730 --> 00:14:20,970
Okay, got it.

267
00:14:29,710 --> 00:14:30,840
I see.

268
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:34,280
But I'm at the place
we were supposed to meet.

269
00:14:35,610 --> 00:14:38,420
That's a shame.
Well, let's meet up next time then.

270
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:39,920
Okay.

271
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:42,290
Hey, Young Ja.

272
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:44,820
No, Lawyer Han.

273
00:14:45,390 --> 00:14:46,660
Oh my gosh, Kang Hyuk.

274
00:14:49,530 --> 00:14:52,160
Kang Hyuk, why are you here
all by yourself?

275
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,110
You've been drinking all alone?

276
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:11,250
Did something happen?

277
00:15:11,680 --> 00:15:12,680
No.

278
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:17,290
Anyway, what brings you here?

279
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:19,620
Thanks.

280
00:15:20,820 --> 00:15:23,690
I was supposed to grab a drink
with a client.

281
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:26,130
But something came up
and they had to cancel.

282
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:28,800
Pour me one, too.

283
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:30,270
Sure.

284
00:15:37,810 --> 00:15:41,350
- Martin Jang?
- Yes. My name is Martin Jang.

285
00:15:42,780 --> 00:15:46,520
So you're living under the name
Martin Jang now, Dad?

286
00:15:46,620 --> 00:15:47,620
That's right.

287
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:51,090
Your grandfather and I mutually agreed
to file for disownment a while ago...

288
00:15:52,020 --> 00:15:53,660
because I had to live as Martin.

289
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:56,030
In order to kick out Chae Hwa Young,

290
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:58,030
your grandfather had to disown me.

291
00:15:58,030 --> 00:16:00,060
Then does that mean you and Mom...

292
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:04,270
- are officially strangers now?
- We may be separated on paper,

293
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,170
but he'll always be my father.

294
00:16:06,570 --> 00:16:07,970
Thanks to him,

295
00:16:07,970 --> 00:16:09,940
I learned how to run a business
as the successor to Dream,

296
00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:14,750
and based on that,
I was able to make all this money.

297
00:16:17,210 --> 00:16:20,220
Try this.
I made your favorite sweet rice drink.

298
00:16:21,450 --> 00:16:25,390
Jang Mi loves it too.
I guess it runs in the family.

299
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:28,760
So you like sweet rice drink too.

300
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:35,830
I used to dream of sitting around
with our kids in a house like this...

301
00:16:36,730 --> 00:16:38,340
eating a meal together.

302
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:43,340
That's right. I didn't know
how big our family would get,

303
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:47,540
but I wanted that simple life
of eating and talking together.

304
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:48,880
You remember that?

305
00:16:50,010 --> 00:16:51,580
We can live like that, Suk Hee.

306
00:16:53,180 --> 00:16:54,350
Let's live like that from now on.

307
00:16:55,490 --> 00:16:57,350
I'll get us a better house.

308
00:17:02,690 --> 00:17:05,500
Jang Mi,
my mom is putting her plan into action,

309
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,700
so come to our house now.

310
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,670
I never thought you'd move...

311
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:14,470
into the same house as Chae Hwa Young.

312
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:16,210
I thought you...

313
00:17:17,470 --> 00:17:20,380
at least had some common sense.

314
00:17:21,650 --> 00:17:26,220
How could you take advantage
of the Chairman's collapse?

315
00:17:26,450 --> 00:17:27,650
As you may have heard,

316
00:17:29,990 --> 00:17:31,960
I'm Jun Ho's Dad.

317
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:34,830
So...

318
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:37,930
that's why you can't leave
Chae Hwa Young's side.

319
00:17:38,330 --> 00:17:39,700
For once in my life...

320
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:42,600
Just once...

321
00:17:43,470 --> 00:17:46,740
I wanted to live with my son
and the woman who gave birth to him...

322
00:17:47,940 --> 00:17:50,840
happily under one roof.

323
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:52,380
And Jun Ho?

324
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:55,810
Does he accept you as his father?

325
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:57,610
To my Jun Ho...

326
00:17:58,950 --> 00:18:00,050
His mother is...

327
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:04,020
Yes.

328
00:18:05,390 --> 00:18:07,460
His mother is a criminal...

329
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:11,230
and his father is the shadow
that helps her.

330
00:18:15,770 --> 00:18:17,900
Hwa Young and I
are one and the same, really.

331
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:27,040
Oh my goodness.

332
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:29,210
- Oh my...
- I'm sorry, it's just...

333
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:32,020
I think I'm a bit drunk.

334
00:18:32,150 --> 00:18:34,150
Your pants are wet.

335
00:18:34,150 --> 00:18:36,820
Why don't you go to the restroom
and dry them off?

336
00:18:37,690 --> 00:18:38,690
Okay.

337
00:18:49,930 --> 00:18:52,840
(Installing
Smart Real-Time Location Tracker)

338
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:03,580
(Manager Lee Kang Hyuk)

339
00:19:11,820 --> 00:19:14,090
- I'm back...
- I'm sorry, Kang Hyuk.

340
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:15,390
No, it's okay.

341
00:19:15,390 --> 00:19:17,590
I think I got a bit worked up
because I'm drunk.

342
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:19,300
I should get going.

343
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,770
(Lawyer Han)

344
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:25,800
What is this?

345
00:19:27,670 --> 00:19:28,770
It's a collection of photos of Jun Ho...

346
00:19:29,610 --> 00:19:33,180
from when he was little until now.

347
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:34,950
It's a cloud link.

348
00:19:35,710 --> 00:19:38,720
The files were too large to send,

349
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:40,850
so I sent you the link instead.

350
00:19:41,350 --> 00:19:43,650
- Why are you giving this to me?
- I guess...

351
00:19:44,590 --> 00:19:46,590
it’s time I let you take your son back.

352
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:52,860
When you click the link I sent
and go to the album,

353
00:19:53,530 --> 00:19:55,430
it's like a diary of his life.

354
00:19:56,530 --> 00:19:58,300
All the photos of Jun Ho are in there.

355
00:20:00,670 --> 00:20:02,410
Since you're Jun Ho's biological father,

356
00:20:04,340 --> 00:20:05,340
you should see them.

357
00:20:07,540 --> 00:20:08,550
Young Ja.

358
00:20:10,950 --> 00:20:11,980
Thank you.

359
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:15,750
This one...

360
00:20:16,450 --> 00:20:17,990
is on me.

361
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:32,970
(My Jun Ho,
A Folder Shared by Han Young Ja)

362
00:20:34,810 --> 00:20:36,440
(My Jun Ho,
A Folder Shared by Han Young Ja)

363
00:20:53,060 --> 00:20:54,360
(Sanghak Middle School)

364
00:20:57,130 --> 00:20:59,460
Mom, Manager Lee took the bait.

365
00:20:59,860 --> 00:21:02,630
I'm tracking his location
in real time now.

366
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:06,000
You are? That's a relief.
I'll be home soon.

367
00:21:06,170 --> 00:21:07,200
You did great, Mom.

368
00:21:08,870 --> 00:21:09,870
Baek Ho.

369
00:21:10,510 --> 00:21:13,540
Did your mother really install an app
on Manager Lee's phone?

370
00:21:14,210 --> 00:21:17,110
With his personality,
there's no way he'd just let that slide.

371
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:18,520
How on earth did she do it?

372
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,820
Well, my mom...

373
00:21:21,490 --> 00:21:24,190
Chae Hwa Young is cornered.

374
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:27,120
She's so furious,
there's no telling what she'll do.

375
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:28,630
That's what I'm most worried about.

376
00:21:28,890 --> 00:21:30,490
What if we do this, Baek Ho?

377
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:33,300
Lee Kang Hyuk is Chae Hwa Young's shadow.

378
00:21:33,730 --> 00:21:36,070
If we just know
where Lee Kang Hyuk is going,

379
00:21:36,370 --> 00:21:38,770
won't we be able to figure out
what Chae Hwa Young is plotting?

380
00:21:38,940 --> 00:21:40,170
That's true,

381
00:21:41,070 --> 00:21:42,810
but Lee Kang Hyuk is so meticulous,

382
00:21:42,810 --> 00:21:44,910
it won't be easy to plant something
on his phone.

383
00:21:45,710 --> 00:21:48,080
We have to exploit his Achilles' heel.

384
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:52,450
He's Jun Ho's Dad, but he can't
step forward. The sorrow of that.

385
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:54,020
But deep down,

386
00:21:54,380 --> 00:21:56,720
he believes he is Jun Ho's father.

387
00:21:57,390 --> 00:21:58,720
He must take pride in that.

388
00:21:59,260 --> 00:22:01,630
And he must have a strong desire
to act like a father.

389
00:22:03,230 --> 00:22:05,630
Even for someone like him,
who's unqualified,

390
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:09,300
if we give him the illusion
that he can play the part of a father,

391
00:22:10,930 --> 00:22:13,800
he'll open the floodgates of misery
with his own hands.

392
00:22:15,310 --> 00:22:17,070
I'm grateful to your mother.

393
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:18,940
She even told us
about Chae Hwa Young's lackey.

394
00:22:19,410 --> 00:22:21,680
It couldn't have been an easy decision
for her to make right now.

395
00:22:22,180 --> 00:22:23,550
She's very brave.

396
00:22:23,750 --> 00:22:26,250
My mom is pretty cool, right?

397
00:22:27,020 --> 00:22:28,050
Yes.

398
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:31,720
I can't even begin to imagine
how your mother feels...

399
00:22:32,290 --> 00:22:33,890
letting Jun Ho go like that.

400
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:36,460
I think my mom has finally
made up her mind.

401
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:38,530
To let Kang Jun Ho go.

402
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:43,270
That's why she put a hacking program
in the cloud link...

403
00:22:43,530 --> 00:22:45,200
that had Kang Jun Ho's growth records,

404
00:22:45,770 --> 00:22:49,010
and Lee Kang Hyuk clicked on it
without suspicion...

405
00:22:49,010 --> 00:22:50,340
thinking it was his son's life story.

406
00:22:58,420 --> 00:23:00,720
How many payments
are we going to miss this month?

407
00:23:01,490 --> 00:23:03,150
We can't go bankrupt.

408
00:23:04,420 --> 00:23:07,290
And no one's jumping at a sale.
This is driving me crazy.

409
00:23:13,460 --> 00:23:16,770
- Where are your manners?
- Is now the time to worry about manners?

410
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:20,340
I just met the head of the linen supplier
in the hotel lobby.

411
00:23:20,670 --> 00:23:23,140
He grabbed me and begged, saying
his company is about to go bankrupt...

412
00:23:23,210 --> 00:23:24,510
because we're so behind on payments.

413
00:23:24,810 --> 00:23:26,440
What is going on
with the hotel's finances?

414
00:23:26,540 --> 00:23:30,080
In business,
cash flow can get tied up temporarily.

415
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:34,150
- It'll be resolved, so stay out of it.
- Now that Grandfather is bedridden,

416
00:23:34,450 --> 00:23:36,450
are you determined to run the company
into the ground?

417
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:39,160
Not to mention
your poor management skills.

418
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:41,060
We'd be lucky
if you weren't embezzling funds.

419
00:23:41,690 --> 00:23:44,090
What? You think you can
just say whatever you want?

420
00:23:44,630 --> 00:23:47,260
I'm the CEO of this company.
Who do you think you are?

421
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:50,670
As CEO,
you should have crisis management skills.

422
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:53,800
This whole situation is a crisis
caused by an incompetent CEO.

423
00:23:54,070 --> 00:23:55,740
If you're a CEO, act like one.

424
00:23:55,770 --> 00:23:58,280
You should be working
to get the hotel's finances back on track.

425
00:23:58,510 --> 00:24:00,140
Are you just going to sit back
and do nothing?

426
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,680
Mind your own business, Oh Jang Mi.

427
00:24:02,150 --> 00:24:04,450
You're only here until
the shareholders' meeting anyway.

428
00:24:04,650 --> 00:24:06,080
Just wait until I become chairman.

429
00:24:06,080 --> 00:24:07,520
You'll be the first to go.

430
00:24:08,950 --> 00:24:10,790
Still can't give up on your dream
of being chairman?

431
00:24:11,120 --> 00:24:15,260
If you can't get the company back
to normal by the shareholders' meeting,

432
00:24:15,330 --> 00:24:16,730
you'll be the one who gets fired first.

433
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:19,430
I'm going to formally propose
your dismissal.

434
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:24,130
I'll make sure everyone knows that you,
Chae Hwa Young, are poison to this hotel.

435
00:24:29,810 --> 00:24:31,240
Unbelievable.

436
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:32,240
Fine, go ahead.

437
00:24:32,510 --> 00:24:34,040
You think
you can persuade the shareholders?

438
00:24:34,540 --> 00:24:36,280
How ridiculous. Who does she think she is?

439
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:38,080
Oh Jang Mi,

440
00:24:38,080 --> 00:24:40,950
none of this would have happened
if you hadn't stolen the bonsai trees.

441
00:24:41,620 --> 00:24:45,660
That wretched woman.
She blocks my path at every single turn.

442
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:49,390
I'm sorry, but that's not possible.

443
00:24:49,790 --> 00:24:52,730
Dream Hotel's recent revenue
has been cut in half.

444
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:55,270
On top of that, there's the owner risk
and ugly rumors flying around.

445
00:24:55,430 --> 00:24:58,470
In this situation, there isn't a bank
in all of this country...

446
00:24:58,470 --> 00:25:01,400
- that would approve such a large amount.
- I'm sorry. I don't think we can.

447
00:25:01,610 --> 00:25:04,070
- It's not going to work.
- You don't meet conditions for a loan.

448
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,380
(Daehan Bank, Baekdu Bank, Taeyang Bank)

449
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:09,480
Mom.

450
00:25:09,550 --> 00:25:13,480
Manager Lee has been going around
to every bank.

451
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,550
It looks like he's trying
to get a loan approved.

452
00:25:15,690 --> 00:25:17,620
The company must be in a really tough spot
right now.

453
00:25:18,690 --> 00:25:19,690
Okay, Mom.

454
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:23,890
Dad, is the hotel really going
to go bankrupt at this rate?

455
00:25:24,660 --> 00:25:25,760
Don't worry, Jang Mi.

456
00:25:26,630 --> 00:25:29,670
This whole plan is just to get rid of
Chae Hwa Young.

457
00:25:29,900 --> 00:25:32,440
So you're saying this is a trap
to lure in Chae Hwa Young?

458
00:25:32,570 --> 00:25:33,570
That's right.

459
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:36,140
Right now, Chae Hwa Young can't get money
from anywhere,

460
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:37,470
but the loan sharks in Myeong-dong.

461
00:25:37,740 --> 00:25:40,540
And if she wants to sell off the hotel's
prime assets and skip the country,

462
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:42,350
the company
needs to be operating normally.

463
00:25:42,710 --> 00:25:45,350
So she'll do whatever it takes
to avoid bankruptcy.

464
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:50,150
So, you plan to use loan sharks
to seize Chae Hwa Young's collateral...

465
00:25:50,490 --> 00:25:52,760
and step in when she tries
to sell off the prime assets?

466
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:56,090
Exactly. I have to let her run herself
into a corner.

467
00:25:56,830 --> 00:25:58,860
That's the only way
she'll take the hand I offer.

468
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:03,200
My goal is to make Chae Hwa Young
give up all her shares...

469
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:04,570
and force her to flee the country.

470
00:26:05,170 --> 00:26:07,570
Of course, I'll catch her
and throw her in prison before that.

471
00:26:08,870 --> 00:26:12,980
- Turn on the TV, now. Hurry.
- Tae Pyung, what's going on?

472
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,410
This afternoon, off the coast of Incheon,

473
00:26:15,410 --> 00:26:18,210
the badly decomposed body of a man
was discovered.

474
00:26:18,420 --> 00:26:20,850
The body was heavily damaged
from being underwater for a long time,

475
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:24,550
but fortunately, his identity
was confirmed through his dental records.

476
00:26:24,890 --> 00:26:26,520
He has been identified
as an auto shop employee...

477
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:27,520
who went missing.

478
00:26:27,590 --> 00:26:30,690
- His name is Kim Bum Seok.
- What's the matter? Do you know him?

479
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:32,700
- An autopsy will be ordered...
- That's Kim Bum Seok from the auto shop.

480
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:35,400
He was on the dashcam footage
when my father was murdered.

481
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:37,130
He was the one who tried to extort money
from Chae Hwa Young.

482
00:26:37,830 --> 00:26:38,870
Who are you?

483
00:26:38,870 --> 00:26:40,140
I'm the person you need.

484
00:26:40,370 --> 00:26:44,610
- Did you follow me? You got a death wish?
- Calm down. Just listen to me.

485
00:26:45,740 --> 00:26:47,140
I'm not with Chae Hwa Young.

486
00:26:47,810 --> 00:26:49,050
Give me the original.

487
00:26:49,610 --> 00:26:50,750
You've got to be kidding me.

488
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:53,880
Lee Kang Hyuk was after him,
and in the end...

489
00:26:54,050 --> 00:26:57,720
Anyway, Chae Hwa Young
will be locked up for good for this.

490
00:26:58,720 --> 00:26:59,720
Baek Ho.

491
00:27:00,060 --> 00:27:02,230
Ssangkal's girlfriend.
She's in danger too.

492
00:27:02,490 --> 00:27:05,000
You're right.
Getting the evidence is important,

493
00:27:05,230 --> 00:27:06,230
but we have to prevent...

494
00:27:06,230 --> 00:27:07,300
any more innocent people
from getting hurt.

495
00:27:07,430 --> 00:27:08,500
Let's move now.

496
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:11,670
From an accidental death
to the possibility of foul play,

497
00:27:11,770 --> 00:27:13,970
the police are investigating
all possibilities.

498
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:16,070
How could you be so sloppy?

499
00:27:16,340 --> 00:27:19,980
I told you to weigh him down with cement
so the body wouldn't surface.

500
00:27:20,180 --> 00:27:21,280
I apologize.

501
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:24,910
But I already got rid of
all the direct evidence back then,

502
00:27:25,250 --> 00:27:27,280
- so you don't need to worry.
- Shut up.

503
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:30,390
Now that he's been identified,
it's only a matter of time...

504
00:27:30,450 --> 00:27:32,260
before the noose tightens around my neck.

505
00:27:33,290 --> 00:27:36,390
I have to stop the cops
from snooping around,

506
00:27:36,390 --> 00:27:38,760
but what do I do? I have no money.

507
00:27:39,560 --> 00:27:42,270
We can get the money.

508
00:27:42,830 --> 00:27:45,840
I just got a discreet call
from the loan sharks in Myeong-dong.

509
00:27:46,170 --> 00:27:47,500
His name is Martin Jang.

510
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:49,710
He's the head
of a major private equity fund...

511
00:27:49,710 --> 00:27:51,340
that operates in Europe and Asia.

512
00:27:51,710 --> 00:27:53,410
I heard he's been watching Dream Hotel.

513
00:27:54,210 --> 00:27:55,310
Martin Jang?

514
00:27:56,350 --> 00:27:57,510
I've heard that name.

515
00:27:57,650 --> 00:27:59,580
They say his financial power
is beyond imagination.

516
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:03,490
We can sell him the prime operating rights
and shares of Dream Hotel for dirt cheap,

517
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:07,920
and in return, we take a kickback.

518
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:10,430
Let's do that.

519
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:14,060
There's no way we'd get caught
for a kickback on a dirt-cheap sale.

520
00:28:14,260 --> 00:28:17,830
Shall I arrange a top-secret meeting?

521
00:28:19,470 --> 00:28:20,900
Luck is on my side.

522
00:28:22,210 --> 00:28:23,370
Martin Jang.

523
00:28:24,870 --> 00:28:26,040
My savior has arrived.

524
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:55,510
(The First Man)

525
00:28:55,670 --> 00:28:57,510
Did you kill Kim Bum Seok?

526
00:28:57,810 --> 00:29:00,280
What does a human life even mean to you?

527
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:03,080
You wouldn't even blink an eye if I died.

528
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:05,480
You had me completely fooled.

529
00:29:05,750 --> 00:29:08,320
You were the one who went through my car
to steal that receipt...

530
00:29:08,450 --> 00:29:11,320
and planted a tracker on my phone, right?

531
00:29:11,860 --> 00:29:14,590
I have proof that Chae Hwa Young
murdered Oh Bok Gil.

532
00:29:14,660 --> 00:29:18,390
Jang Mi, it's Shin Ae Ran.
Please, help me quickly.

533
00:29:20,930 --> 00:29:22,930
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
